BaseInput.body:
import React from "react";
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";
import { DocsProvider } from "../../components/DocsProvider";
import { BaseInputExample } from "../../components/BaseInputExample";

# BaseInput Component

The `BaseInput` component is a styled input used as the foundation for custom inputs like `HbarInput` and `HederaAddressInput`. It supports prefix and suffix elements, and handles error and disabled states.

## Import

```tsx
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";
```

## Props

| Prop          | Type                                  | Default     | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------- | ----------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `value`       | `string`                              | `undefined` | The current input value.                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| `onChange`    | `(value: string) => void`             | -           | Callback fired when the input value changes.                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| `name`        | `string`                              | -           | Name attribute for the input element.                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| `placeholder` | `string`                              | -           | Placeholder text displayed when the input is empty.                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| `error`       | `boolean`                             | `false`     | When `true`, applies error styling to the input border.                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| `tone`        | `"default" \| "success" \| "pending"` | `"default"` | Border emphasis when not in error/disabled. **`pending`** uses a neutral `base-content` tint (e.g. while resolving). **`success`** matches the default idle border by design (no extra green chrome—rely on content for “ok” feedback). |
| `disabled`    | `boolean`                             | `false`     | When `true`, disables the input and applies disabled styling.                                                                                                                                                                           |
| `prefix`      | `ReactNode`                           | -           | Element rendered before the input (e.g., an icon).                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| `suffix`      | `ReactNode`                           | -           | Element rendered after the input (e.g., a button or icon).                                                                                                                                                                              |
| `reFocus`     | `boolean`                             | -           | When `true`, auto-focuses the input and positions cursor at the end. Useful for programmatic focus.                                                                                                                                     |
| `style`       | `CSSProperties`                       | -           | Custom inline styles for the input container.                                                                                                                                                                                           |

## Live Examples

### Basic Usage

<DocsProvider>
  <BaseInputExample placeholder="Enter your name" />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

function BasicInput() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState("");

  return (
    <BaseInput
      value={value}
      onChange={setValue}
      placeholder="Enter your name"
    />
  );
}
```

### With Prefix and Suffix

<DocsProvider>
  <BaseInputExample
    placeholder="0.00"
    prefix={<span style={{ paddingLeft: 12, display: "flex", alignItems: "center", color: "#888" }}>$</span>}
    suffix={<span style={{ paddingRight: 12, display: "flex", alignItems: "center", color: "#888" }}>USD</span>}
  />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

function CurrencyInput() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState("");

  return (
    <BaseInput
      value={value}
      onChange={setValue}
      placeholder="0.00"
      prefix={<span style={{ paddingLeft: 12 }}>$</span>}
      suffix={<span style={{ paddingRight: 12 }}>USD</span>}
    />
  );
}
```

### Error State

<DocsProvider>
  <BaseInputExample
    initialValue="invalid-email"
    placeholder="Enter your email"
    validateEmail={true}
  />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

function InputWithValidation() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState("invalid-email");
  const hasError = value.length > 0 && !value.includes("@");

  return (
    <div>
      <BaseInput
        value={value}
        onChange={setValue}
        placeholder="Enter your email"
        error={hasError}
      />
      {hasError && <p style={{ color: "red" }}>Please enter a valid email</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Disabled State

<DocsProvider>
  <BaseInputExample
    initialValue="Read-only content"
    disabled={true}
  />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { BaseInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

function DisabledInput() {
  return (
    <BaseInput
      value="Read-only content"
      onChange={() => {}}
      disabled={true}
    />
  );
}
```

:::info
`BaseInput` is designed as a building block. For Hedera amounts or address input, use [`HbarInput`](/components/HbarInput) or [`HederaAddressInput`](/components/HederaAddressInput).
:::

Styling.body:
import React, { useMemo } from "react";
import { Address } from "@scaffold-ui/components";
import { DocsProvider } from "../../components/DocsProvider";

# Styling components

## Style Prop

Every component has a `style` prop that you can use to pass custom styles to the top-level element of the component.

| Prop    | Type            | Default | Description                                       |
| ------- | --------------- | ------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `style` | `CSSProperties` | -       | Custom CSS styles (memoize to prevent re-renders) |

⚠️ **Performance Warning**: Always memoize style objects to prevent unnecessary re-renders.

Example:

<DocsProvider>
  <Address
    address="0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045"
    style={useMemo(
      () => ({
        padding: "16px",
        borderRadius: "8px",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1)",
      }),
      [],
    )}
  />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx twoslash
import React, { useMemo } from "react";
import { Address } from "@scaffold-ui/components";
import type { CSSProperties } from "react";

function MyComponent() {
  // Memoized style object
  const customStyle = useMemo(
    () =>
      ({
        padding: "16px",
        borderRadius: "8px",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1)",
      }) as CSSProperties,
    [],
  );

  return (
    <Address
      address="0x1234567890123456789012345678901234567890"
      style={customStyle}
    />
  );
}
```

## Redefining Inner Styles

All Scaffold-UI component styles rely on the default [tailwindcss theme variables](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme#what-are-theme-variables) defined in [styles.css](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/main/packages/components/src/styles.css).

To change the inner styles of components, you need to:

- Check the source code of the component to identify which variable is used for the desired style
- Redefine the variable, and all dependent styles will update accordingly

For example, if you want to change the text color of the Address component, you can check the [source code](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/ea325159a4f733d79c99c7805fb50e4945e96873/packages/components/src/Address/Address.tsx#L82) and see that the `Address` component has the class `text-sui-primary-content`, which uses the `--color-sui-primary-content` variable for the text color. Let's redefine it:

<DocsProvider>
  <Address
    address="0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045"
    style={useMemo(
      () => ({
        "--color-sui-primary-content": "green",
        padding: "16px",
        borderRadius: "8px",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1)",
      }),
      [],
    )}
  />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx twoslash
import React, { useMemo } from "react";
import { Address } from "@scaffold-ui/components";
import type { CSSProperties } from "react";

function MyComponent() {
  // Memoized style object
  const customStyle = useMemo(
    () =>
      ({
        "--color-sui-primary-content": "green",
        padding: "16px",
        borderRadius: "8px",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1)",
      }) as CSSProperties,
    [],
  );

  return (
    <Address
      address="0x1234567890123456789012345678901234567890"
      style={customStyle}
    />
  );
}
```

Theming.body:
import React, { useMemo } from "react";
import { DocsProvider } from "../../components/DocsProvider";
import { HbarInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

# Theming

:::info
Before reading this page, we recommend checking out the [Styling](/components/Styling) page to understand the basics of styling Scaffold-UI components.
:::

## Typography (Hedera brand alignment)

Hedera’s brand guidelines specify **Styrene A** as the primary typeface (commercial license required) and **Montserrat** as the replacement font for broader use (presentations, documents, and web when Styrene is not licensed).

**This library**

- Exposes **`--font-sui-family`**. Wrapped components use the `font-sui` utility (`font-family: var(--font-sui-family)`).
- **Default in `@scaffold-ui/components`:** stack starts with **Montserrat** (load it yourself, e.g. [Google Fonts](https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Montserrat)) so open-source consumers stay aligned without bundling Styrene.
- **With a Styrene license:** set the same stack your brand team approves, e.g.  
  `:root { --font-sui-family: "Styrene A Web", "Montserrat", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; }`  
  after loading `@font-face` for Styrene.

**Import order:** load font CSS (or `next/font`) first, then `@scaffold-ui/components/styles.css`, then any overrides to `:root` / `.dark`.

## Dark Theme

All Scaffold-UI component styles use theme variables defined in [packages/components/src/styles.css](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/main/packages/components/src/styles.css).

The stylesheet includes dark theme styles that automatically apply based on your theme configuration.

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *, [data-theme=dark], [data-theme=dark] *));

...

@variant dark {
  --color-sui-primary: #212638;
  ...
}

```

To enable dark mode, add either a `.dark` class or a `[data-theme=dark]` attribute to a parent element (typically the `<html>` or `<body>` tag). This will automatically apply the dark variant colors to all child components.

### Setup

- **Next.js apps**: We recommend using the `next-themes` library. See example implementations of [SwitchTheme](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/main/example/app/components/SwitchTheme.tsx) and [ThemeProvider](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/main/example/app/components/ThemeProvider.tsx).
- **create-hbar apps**: These components are already included and configured.

### Live Example

Use the theme switcher in the bottom left corner to see how the component colors change between light and dark modes.

<DocsProvider>
  <HbarInput placeholder="Amount in HBAR or USD" />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx twoslash
import React from "react";
import { HbarInput } from "@scaffold-ui/components";

<HbarInput placeholder="Amount in HBAR or USD" />;
```

## Customizing Theme Colors Globally

You can override the default theme colors by redefining CSS variables in your global stylesheet **after** importing `@scaffold-ui/components/styles.css`.

```css
/* Override Scaffold UI theme colors */
:root {
  --color-sui-primary: #ff4444;
  --color-sui-primary-subtle: #ff9999;
  ...
}

/* Dark mode - explicit selectors matching the custom-variant definition */
.dark,
[data-theme="dark"] {
  --color-sui-primary: #654321;
  --color-sui-primary-subtle: #987654;
  ...
}

```

Purple / blue accents and dark surfaces in Hedera marketing can be approximated with the defaults already tuned in `styles.css`; adjust `--color-sui-primary`, `--color-sui-accent`, and related tokens to match your approved brand palette.

## Token reference (`@scaffold-ui/components`)

Defined in [styles.css](https://github.com/buidler-labs/scaffold-ui/blob/main/packages/components/src/styles.css) (source of truth). Light values live in `@theme`; dark overrides in `@variant dark`.

| Token | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `--font-sui-family` | Font stack for all `DefaultStylesWrapper` / `font-sui` usage |
| `--color-sui-primary` | Primary brand / actions |
| `--color-sui-primary-subtle` | Subtle surfaces, borders |
| `--color-sui-primary-neutral` | Neutral surface |
| `--color-sui-primary-content` | Text/icons on primary |
| `--color-sui-accent` | Accent |
| `--color-sui-base-content` | Main body text |
| `--color-sui-success` | Success |
| `--color-sui-warning` | Warning |
| `--color-sui-error` | Error (e.g. toasts); inputs may use primary for invalid state |
| `--color-sui-input-border` | Input border |
| `--color-sui-input-background` | Input background |
| `--color-sui-input-text` | Input text |
| `--color-sui-input-placeholder` | Placeholder |
| `--color-sui-input-border-error` | Invalid input border |
| `--color-sui-input-border-disabled` | Disabled input border |
| `--color-sui-skeleton-base` | Skeleton base |
| `--color-sui-skeleton-highlight` | Skeleton highlight |

## `@scaffold-ui/debug-contracts`

That package imports component styles and adds more tokens (e.g. `--color-sui-base-100`, `--color-sui-neutral`, `--color-sui-neutral-content`) for forms and buttons. Override those in your global CSS **after** `@scaffold-ui/debug-contracts/styles.css` if you use the debugger UI.

## Customizing fonts globally

```css
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;600;700&display=swap");
@import "@scaffold-ui/components/styles.css";

:root {
  --font-sui-family: "Montserrat", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
}
```

With Styrene (licensed) + Montserrat:

```css
:root {
  --font-sui-family: "Styrene A Web", "Montserrat", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
}
```

(Define `@font-face` for Styrene per your license; do not rely on unlicensed third-party font hosts in production.)

useAddress.body:
import React from "react";
import { useAddress } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
import { DocsProvider } from "../../components/DocsProvider";

# useAddress Hook

The `useAddress` hook formats EVM addresses (checksum, short form), builds a **block explorer link** for the given `chain` (HashScan-style paths on Hedera), and generates a **blockie** image URL. Pass a `chain` from `viem/chains` (e.g. `hedera`, `hederaTestnet`) for correct explorer URLs.

## Import

```tsx
import { useAddress } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
import { hederaTestnet } from "viem/chains";

const { checkSumAddress, blockExplorerAddressLink, isValidAddress, shortAddress, blockieUrl } = useAddress({
  address: "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045",
  chain: hederaTestnet,
});
```

## Parameters

| Parameter | Type                   | Default  | Description                                                                                         |
| --------- | ---------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `address` | `Address` _(optional)_ | -        | The EVM address to process.                                                                         |
| `chain`   | `Chain` _(optional)_   | `hederaTestnet` | Used for explorer links. Defaults to **`hederaTestnet`** when omitted; pass `hedera` from `viem/chains` for mainnet. |

## Return Values

| Property                   | Type                   | Description                                      |
| -------------------------- | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `checkSumAddress`          | `Address \| undefined` | Checksummed address when input is valid.         |
| `ens`                      | `undefined`            | Reserved; not populated in this build.           |
| `ensAvatar`                | `undefined`            | Reserved; not populated in this build.           |
| `isEnsNameLoading`         | `false`                | Reserved.                                        |
| `blockExplorerAddressLink` | `string`               | Explorer URL for the address on the given chain. |
| `isValidAddress`           | `boolean`              | Whether the input is a valid EVM address.        |
| `shortAddress`             | `string \| undefined`  | Short form (`0x1234…5678`).                      |
| `blockieUrl`               | `string \| undefined`  | Deterministic blockie data URL.                  |

## Live Example

export function UseAddressBasicExample() {
  const address = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const { checkSumAddress, shortAddress, blockExplorerAddressLink } = useAddress({ address });
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Short: {shortAddress}</p>
      <p>
        Full with explorer link:{" "}
        <a
          href={blockExplorerAddressLink}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          {checkSumAddress}
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}

<DocsProvider>
  <UseAddressBasicExample />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { useAddress } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";

function AddressDisplay() {
  const address = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const { checkSumAddress, shortAddress, blockExplorerAddressLink } = useAddress({ address });

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Short: {shortAddress}</p>
      <p>
        <a
          href={blockExplorerAddressLink}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          {checkSumAddress}
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

useBalance.body:
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useBalance } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
import { DocsProvider } from "../../components/DocsProvider";
import { hederaTestnet } from "viem/chains";

# useBalance Hook

The `useBalance` hook fetches and watches an address balance on a given chain, pairing live USD conversion. For **Hedera** chains, the native currency (HBAR) price is fetched automatically; for other chains, the price comes from Uniswap or `NETWORKS_EXTRA_DATA`.

## Import

```tsx
import { useBalance } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
const {
  displayUsdMode,
  toggleDisplayUsdMode,
  formattedBalance,
  balanceInUsd,
  balance,
  isBalanceLoading,
  isBalanceError,
  isNativeCurrencyPriceLoading,
  isNativeCurrencyPriceError,
  isLoading,
  isError,
} = useBalance({
  address: "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045",
  chain: hederaTestnet,
  defaultUsdMode: true,
});
```

## Parameters

| Parameter        | Type                   | Default | Description                                                                 |
| ---------------- | ---------------------- | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `address`        | `Address` _(optional)_ | -       | The address to watch. When omitted, the hook returns zeroed balance values. |
| `chain`          | `Chain`                | -       | The **viem** chain configuration used for fetching balances and USD prices. |
| `defaultUsdMode` | `boolean` _(optional)_ | `false` | If `true` and price data is available, show USD values by default.          |

## Return Values

| Property                       | Type                                | Description                                                                 |
| ------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `displayUsdMode`               | `boolean`                           | Whether the display is currently set to USD.                                |
| `toggleDisplayUsdMode`         | `() => void`                        | Toggle between native and USD display (only active when price data exists). |
| `formattedBalance`             | `number`                            | Native balance normalized with `formatEther`.                               |
| `balanceInUsd`                 | `number`                            | USD value derived from `formattedBalance * nativeCurrencyPrice`.            |
| `balance`                      | `GetBalanceReturnType \| undefined` | Raw wagmi balance payload containing value, decimals, and symbol.           |
| `isBalanceLoading`             | `boolean`                           | Loading state for the balance fetch.                                        |
| `isBalanceError`               | `boolean`                           | Error state for the balance fetch.                                          |
| `isNativeCurrencyPriceLoading` | `boolean`                           | Loading state for fetching the native currency price.                       |
| `isNativeCurrencyPriceError`   | `boolean`                           | Error state for fetching the native currency price.                         |
| `isLoading`                    | `boolean`                           | Combined loading state: balance data or price is still loading.             |
| `isError`                      | `boolean`                           | Combined error state: balance data or price failed to load.                 |

:::info
USD display is enabled only after the native currency price has been fetched. If the price is not available, toggling to USD is disabled and native balance is shown.
:::

## Live Examples

### Basic Usage

Display a live balance with an inline USD toggle.

export function UseBalanceBasicExample() {
  const address = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const {
    formattedBalance,
    balanceInUsd,
    displayUsdMode,
    toggleDisplayUsdMode,
    isLoading,
  } = useBalance({
    address,
    chain: hederaTestnet,
  });

return (

<div>
  <p>Balance: {displayUsdMode ? `$${balanceInUsd.toLocaleString()}` : `${formattedBalance.toLocaleString()} HBAR`}</p>
  <button
    onClick={toggleDisplayUsdMode}
    disabled={isLoading}
  >
    Toggle USD / HBAR
  </button>
</div>
); }

<DocsProvider>
  <UseBalanceBasicExample />
  <div style={{ height: 12 }} />

</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { useBalance } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
import { hederaTestnet } from "viem/chains";

function BalanceWithToggle() {
  const address = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const { formattedBalance, balanceInUsd, displayUsdMode, toggleDisplayUsdMode, isLoading } = useBalance({
    address,
    chain: hederaTestnet,
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <p>
        Balance: {displayUsdMode ? `$${balanceInUsd.toLocaleString()}` : `${formattedBalance.toLocaleString()} HBAR`}
      </p>
      <button
        onClick={toggleDisplayUsdMode}
        disabled={isLoading}
      >
        Toggle USD / HBAR
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Loading and Error States

Handle asynchronous fetch states while keeping the toggle experience consistent.

export function UseBalanceLoadingErrorExample() {
  const [isValidAddress, setIsValidAddress] = useState(true);
  const validAddress = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const brokenAddress = "0x";
  const {
    formattedBalance,
    balanceInUsd,
    displayUsdMode,
    toggleDisplayUsdMode,
    isLoading,
    isError,
  } = useBalance({
    address: isValidAddress ? validAddress : brokenAddress,
    chain: hederaTestnet,
    defaultUsdMode: true,
  });

if (isLoading) return <p>Fetching balance…</p>;
if (isError) return (

<div>
  <p style={{ color: "red" }}>Could not fetch balance</p>
  <button
    style={{
      display: "block",
      padding: "8px",
      background: "#dae8ff",
      borderRadius: "4px",
      marginTop: "4px",
      border: "none",
      cursor: "pointer",
      color: "#000",
    }}
    onClick={() => setIsValidAddress((v) => !v)}
  >
    Fetch balance of the valid address
  </button>
</div>
);

return (

<div>
<p>Balance: {displayUsdMode ? `$${balanceInUsd.toLocaleString()}` : `${formattedBalance.toLocaleString()} HBAR`}</p>
<button onClick={toggleDisplayUsdMode}>Toggle USD / HBAR</button>

      <button
        style={{ display: "block", padding: "8px", background: "#dae8ff", borderRadius: "4px", marginTop: "4px", border: "none", cursor: "pointer", color: "#000" }}
        onClick={() => setIsValidAddress((v) => !v)}
      >
        Try to fetch balance of the broken address
      </button>
    </div>

);
}

<DocsProvider>
  <UseBalanceLoadingErrorExample />
</DocsProvider>

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useBalance } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
import { hederaTestnet } from "viem/chains";

function BalanceWithLoadingStates() {
  const [isValidAddress, setIsValidAddress] = useState(true);
  const validAddress = "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045";
  const brokenAddress = "0x";
  const { formattedBalance, balanceInUsd, displayUsdMode, toggleDisplayUsdMode, isLoading, isError } = useBalance({
    address: isValidAddress ? validAddress : brokenAddress,
    chain: hederaTestnet,
    defaultUsdMode: true,
  });

  if (isLoading) return <p>Fetching balance…</p>;
  if (isError)
    return (
      <div>
        <p style={{ color: "red" }}>Could not fetch balance</p>
        <button
          style={{
            display: "block",
            padding: "8px",
            background: "#dae8ff",
            borderRadius: "4px",
            marginTop: "4px",
            border: "none",
            cursor: "pointer",
            color: "#000",
          }}
          onClick={() => setIsValidAddress((v) => !v)}
        >
          Fetch balance of the valid address
        </button>
      </div>
    );

  return (
    <div>
      <p>
        Balance: {displayUsdMode ? `$${balanceInUsd.toLocaleString()}` : `${formattedBalance.toLocaleString()} HBAR`}
      </p>
      <button onClick={toggleDisplayUsdMode}>Toggle USD / HBAR</button>
      <button
        style={{
          display: "block",
          padding: "8px",
          background: "#dae8ff",
          borderRadius: "4px",
          marginTop: "4px",
          border: "none",
          cursor: "pointer",
          color: "#000",
        }}
        onClick={() => setIsValidAddress((v) => !v)}
      >
        Try to fetch balance of the broken address
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

useCreateTopic.body:
# useCreateTopic Hook

`useCreateTopic` submits a **Consensus Service (HCS) topic create** transaction via [`useNativeTransaction`](/hooks/useNativeTransaction). It builds a `TopicCreateTransaction` from `@hiero-ledger/sdk`, optionally sets a memo, and returns the wallet’s `transactionId`.

The hook does **not** connect to a wallet itself. You must call [`setNativeTransactionSigner`](/hooks/useNativeTransaction) in your app, and usually pass **`ensureReady`** so the user is connected before `mutate`.

## Peer dependency

Requires **`@hiero-ledger/sdk`** (same major as your app).

```bash
pnpm add @hiero-ledger/sdk
```

## Import

```tsx
import { useCreateTopic, type CreateTopicParams, type UseCreateTopicOptions } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
import { useCreateTopic } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
import { useHederaSigner } from "./useHederaSigner"; // your wallet hook

function CreateTopicPanel() {
  const { requireProvider } = useHederaSigner();
  const createTopic = useCreateTopic({
    ensureReady: () => {
      requireProvider();
    },
  });

  return (
    <button
      type="button"
      disabled={createTopic.isPending}
      onClick={() => createTopic.mutate({ memo: "My app topic" })}
    >
      {createTopic.isPending ? "Creating…" : "Create topic"}
    </button>
  );
}
```

Omit **`ensureReady`** if you only rely on **`CapabilityError`** from `sendTransaction` when no signer is set.

## Options

| Option          | Type           | Description                                                                 |
| --------------- | -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `ensureReady?` | `() => void`   | Called at the start of each mutation; throw if the wallet/session is not ready. |

## Mutation variables (`CreateTopicParams`)

| Property | Type       | Description                          |
| -------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `memo?`  | `string`   | Optional topic memo (trimmed).       |

Call `mutate()` or `mutate({})` for a topic with no memo.

## Return value

Returns a **TanStack Query `useMutation`** result (`mutate`, `mutateAsync`, `isPending`, `isError`, `data`, `error`, etc.).

On success, **`data`** is:

| Property          | Type     | Description        |
| ----------------- | -------- | ------------------ |
| `transactionId`   | `string` | From the wallet response. |

## Errors

- **`CapabilityError`** — No native signer configured ([`useNativeTransaction`](/hooks/useNativeTransaction)).
- **`Error("No transactionId returned from wallet")`** — Signer returned an empty response.
- Any error thrown from **`ensureReady`** (e.g. “Connect a Hedera wallet first”).

useHederaAccountId.body:
# useHederaAccountId Hook

The `useHederaAccountId` hook resolves a Hedera account ID (`0.0.n`) for a checksummed EVM address using the mirror node (same-origin `/api/hedera` or injected resolver).

## Import

```tsx
import { useHederaAccountId, type HederaAccountIdStatus } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
const { accountId, status, isLoading } = useHederaAccountId(
  "0xd8da6bf26964af9d7eed9e03e53415d37aa96045",
  296,
);
```

## Parameters

| Parameter    | Type                  | Default | Description                                                      |
| ------------ | --------------------- | ------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `evmAddress` | `string \| undefined` | -       | EVM address (`0x…`) to resolve.                                  |
| `chainId`    | `number` _(optional)_ | `296`   | Chain ID for network mapping (`296` testnet, `295` mainnet).     |

## Return Values

| Property    | Type                      | Description                                                                      |
| ----------- | ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `accountId` | `string \| null`          | Hedera account ID (e.g. `"0.0.8041897"`) when resolved; `null` otherwise.       |
| `status`    | `HederaAccountIdStatus`   | One of `"idle"`, `"pending"`, `"success"`, `"not-found"`, `"error"`.             |
| `isLoading` | `boolean`                 | `true` while the first fetch is in flight (no cached data yet).                  |

### Status values

| Status        | Meaning                                                                       |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `"idle"`      | No address to resolve (input cleared).                                        |
| `"pending"`   | First fetch in flight for this query (no cached data yet).                    |
| `"success"`   | Mirror returned an account ID (`accountId` is set).                           |
| `"not-found"` | Mirror responded: no Hedera account for this EVM address on this network.     |
| `"error"`     | Request failed (network, 5xx, thrown resolver, etc.).                         |

## Example

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { useHederaAccountId } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";

function AccountIdLookup({ evmAddress }: { evmAddress: string }) {
  const { accountId, status, isLoading } = useHederaAccountId(evmAddress, 296);

  if (isLoading) return <p>Resolving…</p>;

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Status: {status}</p>
      {accountId ? <p>Account ID: {accountId}</p> : <p>No Hedera account found.</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Configuring resolution

The library does not call mirror-node directly. Your app owns the data source. Configure once at startup:

- **Same-origin API (default):** If your app serves `GET /api/hedera?evm=…&network=…`, no configuration needed.
- **Custom base URL:** `setHederaAccountIdApiBase('https://your-api.com')`
- **Custom resolver:** `setHederaAccountIdResolver((evmAddress, network) => Promise<string | null>)`

```tsx
import { setHederaAccountIdApiBase, setHederaAccountIdResolver } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";

// Option A: custom base URL
setHederaAccountIdApiBase("https://your-api.com");

// Option B: custom resolver
setHederaAccountIdResolver(async (evmAddress, network) => {
  const res = await fetch(`/api/hedera?evm=${evmAddress}&network=${network}`);
  const data = await res.json();
  return data.accountId ?? null;
});
```

## Related

- **[useHederaEvmAddress](/hooks/useHederaEvmAddress)** — Reverse direction: Hedera account ID → EVM address.
- **[HederaAddress](/components/HederaAddress)** — Display component that uses both hooks for bidirectional resolution.
- **[useHederaAddressInput](/hooks/useHederaAddressInput)** — Input validation hook with built-in bidirectional resolution.

useHederaAddressInput.body:
# useHederaAddressInput Hook

The `useHederaAddressInput` hook validates and resolves Hedera address input in **native** form (`0.0.n`) or **EVM** form (`0x…`). It debounces the value, runs mirror-backed resolution both ways, and exposes a checksummed `evmAddress` when valid. The [`HederaAddressInput`](/components/HederaAddressInput) component uses this hook for its logic; you can use it directly to build a custom input UI.

## Import

```tsx
import {
  useHederaAddressInput,
  type UseHederaAddressInputOptions,
  type UseHederaAddressInputResult,
} from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
const {
  evmAddress,
  shortEvmAddress,
  accountIdFromEvm,
  error,
  warning,
  isNativeFormat,
  isEvmFormat,
  isLoading,
  isLoadingAccountIdFromEvm,
  isResolving,
} = useHederaAddressInput({
  value: inputValue,
  chainId: 296,
  debounceDelay: 400,
});
```

## Parameters

| Parameter       | Type                  | Default | Description                                                              |
| --------------- | --------------------- | ------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `value`         | `string`              | -       | Raw input text (native account ID or EVM address). Trimmed internally.   |
| `chainId`       | `number` _(optional)_ | `296`   | Chain ID for network mapping (e.g. `296` testnet, `295` mainnet).        |
| `debounceDelay` | `number` _(optional)_ | `400`   | Debounce delay in milliseconds before validation and mirror lookups run. |

## Return values

| Property                    | Type                   | Description                                                                                                            |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `evmAddress`                | `Address \| undefined` | Checksummed EVM address when input is valid EVM **or** valid native resolved to EVM.                                   |
| `displayAccountId`          | `string \| undefined`  | The debounced native `0.0.n` when input matches native format.                                                         |
| `shortEvmAddress`           | `string \| undefined`  | Short display form of `evmAddress` (e.g. `0x1234…5678`).                                                               |
| `isLoading`                 | `boolean`              | `true` while resolving **native → EVM** (mirror). Same flag `HederaAddressInput` uses to disable the field when unset. |
| `error`                     | `string \| undefined`  | Blocking validation or mirror error (invalid format, account not found, etc.).                                         |
| `warning`                   | `string \| undefined`  | Non-blocking issues (no EVM alias, unmapped EVM on network, mirror verification failure).                              |
| `isNativeFormat`            | `boolean`              | Whether debounced value matches `0.0.n`.                                                                               |
| `isEvmFormat`               | `boolean`              | Whether debounced value is a 42-char `0x` hex string.                                                                  |
| `accountIdFromEvm`          | `string \| undefined`  | Hedera account ID resolved from EVM when applicable.                                                                   |
| `isLoadingAccountIdFromEvm` | `boolean`              | `true` while resolving **EVM → account ID**.                                                                           |
| `isResolving`               | `boolean`              | `true` while either mirror lookup is in progress.                                                                      |

:::info
`isLoading` is only the native → EVM path. EVM → account ID resolution uses `isLoadingAccountIdFromEvm` and does not set `isLoading`.
:::

## Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useHederaAddressInput } from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";

function CustomHederaField() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState("");
  const { evmAddress, accountIdFromEvm, error, warning, isResolving } = useHederaAddressInput({
    value,
    chainId: 296,
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        value={value}
        onChange={(e) => setValue(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="0.0.12345 or 0x…"
        aria-busy={isResolving && !error ? true : undefined}
      />
      {error ? <p role="alert">{error}</p> : null}
      {warning && !error ? <p role="status">{warning}</p> : null}
      {evmAddress ? <p>Resolved EVM: {evmAddress}</p> : null}
      {accountIdFromEvm ? <p>Account ID: {accountIdFromEvm}</p> : null}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Related

- **[HederaAddressInput](/components/HederaAddressInput)** — Styled input built on this hook.
- **Resolver setup:** The library uses configurable resolvers (default: same-origin API routes). Configure with `setHederaAccountIdResolver` / `setHederaEvmAddressResolver` or `setHederaAccountIdApiBase` / `setHederaEvmAddressApiBase` from `@scaffold-ui/hooks`. See the [HederaAddressInput](/components/HederaAddressInput) page for the expected endpoint shapes.

useNativeTransaction.body:
# useNativeTransaction Hook

The `useNativeTransaction` hook sends **native Hedera transactions** (HTS, HCS, CryptoTransfer, etc.) through the Hedera namespace. It is the native counterpart to EVM contract writes (e.g. `useScaffoldWriteContract`). The host app must inject a signer via `setNativeTransactionSigner`; if none is set, `sendTransaction` throws **CapabilityError** so the UI can prompt the user to connect a Hedera-capable wallet.

## Import

```tsx
import {
  useNativeTransaction,
  setNativeTransactionSigner,
  CapabilityError,
  type NativeTransaction,
  type NativeTransactionResponse,
  type NativeTransactionSigner,
} from "@scaffold-ui/hooks";
```

## Usage

```tsx
// 1. In app setup (e.g. after wallet connect with hedera namespace), set the signer:
setNativeTransactionSigner(async (tx) => {
  const response = await hederaClient.execute(tx); // or wallet.signAndExecute(tx)
  return { transactionId: response.transactionId.toString() };
});

// 2. In a component:
const { sendTransaction, isSending, error, clearError } = useNativeTransaction();

const handleTransfer = async () => {
  try {
    const response = await sendTransaction(
      new TransferTransaction().addHbarTransfer(senderId, new Hbar(-10)).addHbarTransfer(receiverId, new Hbar(10)),
    );
    console.log("Tx ID:", response?.transactionId);
  } catch (e) {
    if (e instanceof CapabilityError) {
      // Show HederaCapabilityBadge or "Connect a Hedera wallet"
    }
  }
};
```

## Return Values

| Property          | Type                                                                         | Description                                                                          |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `sendTransaction` | `(tx: NativeTransaction) => Promise<NativeTransactionResponse \| undefined>` | Submit a native Hedera transaction. Throws **CapabilityError** if no signer was set. |
| `isSending`       | `boolean`                                                                    | `true` while a transaction is being signed and submitted.                            |
| `error`           | `Error \| null`                                                              | Last error (user rejection, network failure, or CapabilityError).                    |
| `clearError`      | `() => void`                                                                 | Reset `error` to `null`.                                                             |

## CapabilityError

When the connected session does not support the Hedera namespace (or no signer was set), `sendTransaction` throws **CapabilityError**. Catch it and surface it in the UI (e.g. with HederaCapabilityBadge or a message like "Connect a wallet that supports native Hedera (HashPack, Blade)").

```tsx
try {
  await sendTransaction(tx);
} catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof CapabilityError) {
    setMessage("Native Hedera not available. Connect HashPack or Blade.");
  }
}
```

## Setting the signer

The hook does not talk to the wallet directly. The app must call **setNativeTransactionSigner(signer)** with a function that:

1. Accepts a Hedera SDK transaction (e.g. `TransferTransaction`, `TokenAssociateTransaction`).
2. Signs and executes it (via Reown AppKit Hedera adapter, HashPack `window.hedera`, Blade, or your own client).
3. Returns a promise that resolves to at least `{ transactionId: string }`.

If your app uses Reown AppKit with the Hedera adapter, wire the adapter’s execute method to this signer. If you use HashPack or Blade, use their API to sign and submit the transaction and return the response shape above.

## Types (no @hashgraph/sdk dependency)

The hooks package does not depend on `@hashgraph/sdk`. **NativeTransaction** is typed as `unknown`; the app passes SDK transaction instances. **NativeTransactionResponse** is `{ transactionId: string; [key: string]: unknown }`. Your signer can return the full SDK `TransactionResponse`; the hook only requires `transactionId`.

